# UDS Content Schema

Per-component spec content lives in `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/spec.json`.
The Guidelines tab on every component page is rendered at runtime from
this JSON by `uds-docs/app/(site)/[componentId]/GuidelinesTab.tsx` (the
client component that consumes `getComponentSpec(id)` from
`lib/uds-data.ts`). Editing the JSON is how spec content is updated.

## Source of truth

- **Schema:** `uds-docs/uds/schemas/spec.schema.json` — defines every field
- **One file per component:** `uds-docs/uds/components/button/spec.json`,
  `uds-docs/uds/components/text-input/spec.json`, etc.

## Rules

1. **Edit JSON, not JSX.** When updating a component's description,
   props, events, slots, accessibility, etc., edit
   `uds/components/<id>/spec.json`. `GuidelinesTab.tsx` picks it up
   automatically via the client-side fetch in `ComponentPageClient`.
2. **New components need a folder first.** Adding a new component
   requires creating `uds/components/<id>/` with at least: `spec.json`,
   `status.json`, `changelog.json`, `examples/manifest.json`, one
   example HTML file, and the empty `<id>.css`. Use the
   `new-component` skill to scaffold all of these correctly.
3. **Empty fields are hidden.** The renderer skips sections where the
   field is null/empty. There's no need to add placeholder text — just
   leave the field empty until the spec is ready.
4. **Don't hardcode component-id branches in the React renderer.** The
   `GuidelinesTab` / `CodeTab` / `ExamplesTab` etc. components must stay
   data-driven. No `if (componentId === 'button')` paths in the renderer.
5. **Drafts use `"draft": true`.** That hides the component from the
   live site. Add `?draft=1` to any URL to view drafts with a watermark.
6. **Deferred sections (motion, responsive) stay null.** UDS doesn't
   have motion or breakpoint tokens yet. Don't fill these in with
   arbitrary values.
7. **Reference the schema.** Every `spec.json` should start with
   `"$schema": "../../schemas/spec.schema.json"` so editors can validate.

## Required minimum for a new component spec.json

```json
{
  "$schema": "../../schemas/spec.schema.json",
  "component": "<id>",
  "title": "<Title>",
  "description": "<one paragraph>",
  "whenToUse": "<one or two sentences>",
  "whenNotToUse": "<one or two sentences with alternative>",
  "dependencies": {
    "css": ["uds/components/<id>/<id>.css"],
    "js": []
  },
  "accessibility": {
    "keyboard": [
      { "key": "Tab", "action": "Move focus" }
    ]
  },
  "owner": { "designer": "Unassigned", "developer": "Unassigned" }
}
```

## Spec completeness

The Guidelines tab shows a "Spec X/Y" pill next to the component title.
The completeness count comes from filled fields in the JSON. Aim for 80%+
before marking a component Production Ready.

## Schema field reference (essential)

- `props[]` — `{ name, type, default, required, enum, description }` — what the Storybook web component should accept
- `events[]` — `{ name, description, payload }` — what the component should dispatch
- `slots[]` — `{ name, description }` — content regions inside the component
- `states[]` — `{ name, description, hasVisual }` — interactive states (default, hover, focus, disabled, error, loading, empty)
- `accessibility.keyboard[]` — `{ key, action }`
- `accessibility.screenReader[]` — `{ trigger, announcement }`
- `accessibility.wcag[]` — `{ criterion, level, howMet }`
- `accessibility.contrast[]` — `{ foreground, background, ratio, passes }`
- `acceptanceCriteria[]` — strings; this is also the ship checklist
- `dosDonts.dos[]` / `dosDonts.donts[]` — strings
- `commonlyPairedWith[]` — component IDs
- `implReference: { exampleId }` — pointer to an entry in `examples/manifest.json` (used by Implementation Reference panel)

See `uds-docs/uds/schemas/spec.schema.json` for the full schema.

## Sync with Storybook

When the spec changes:
1. Update `uds/components/<id>/spec.json`
2. Add a SITE_CHANGELOG entry per `uds-site-changelog.mdc`
3. Append a per-component changelog entry to
   `uds/components/<id>/changelog.json`
4. Run `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh` to refresh
   `uds/CHANGELOG.json`
5. File a Storybook issue if the production component needs to update
   to match
